'''Khendum Choden''' [[Ph.D.]] is a poet, author, and the first [[Bhutan]]ese Ph.D.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://newsuc.utep.edu/index.php/news-latest/1011-utep-celebrates-130th-commencement |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222202547/http://newsuc.utep.edu/index.php/news-latest/1011-utep-celebrates-130th-commencement |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2014-02-22 |title=UTEP’s 130th Commencement Celebrates More Than 2,600 Major Milestones |publisher=Newsuc.utep.edu |date=2013-05-17 |accessdate=2014-02-20 }}</ref> graduate of the [[University of Texas at El Paso]] (UTEP). She is the daughter of a diplomat from the [[Kingdom of Bhutan]] and has also lived in Bangladesh, India and the United States. She was educated at [[Yangchenphug Higher Secondary School]], then in Humanities High School in New York, USA, graduating in 2001. She started a course in Business Management and Economics in [[Stony Brook University]], graduating in 2005, and has a doctoral degree in International Business/ Information Systems from UTEP. She was awarded the UTEP [[Dodson Fellowship]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.10150484728636160.364527.184026786159&type=3 |title=Natalicio Scholarship and Dodson Fellowship Recipients |publisher=Facebook.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> and the Marcus Jonathan Hunt Graduate Fellowship.
She founded the Bhutanese Students Association at [[UTEP]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fq0p4BiMct0 |title=UTEP Centennial Exhibition at El Paso International Airport |publisher=Youtube.com |date=2014-01-24 |accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> and served as the President of the [[Voluntary association|Association]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utepprospector.com/news/bhutanese-students-send-help-back-home-1.1034315#.UvQZgPb5HHM |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221214700/http://www.utepprospector.com/news/bhutanese-students-send-help-back-home-1.1034315 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2014-02-21 |title=Bhutanese students send help back home |publisher=Utepprospector.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref> at the University of Texas at El Paso, donating money to the victims of an earthquake that hit Bhutan in 2009.
