{{Infobox football biography | name = Lyès Saïdi | image = | caption = | fullname = Lyès Saïdi | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|8|24|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Sidi Aïch]], [[Algeria]] | height = | position = [[Defensive midfielder]] | currentclub = [[MC Oran]] | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = SS Sidi Aïch | years1 = {{0|0000}}–2009 | clubs1 = ORB Akbou | caps1 = - | goals1 = - | years2 = 2009–2012 | clubs2 = [[JS Kabylie]] | caps2 = 34 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2012–2013 | clubs3 = [[ASO Chlef]] | caps3 = 3 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2013–2015 | clubs4 = [[MC Oran]] | caps4 = 27 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Algeria Military national football team|Algeria Military]] | nationalcaps1 = - | nationalgoals1 = - | medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{ALG}}}} {{MedalSport|Men's [[World Military Cup|Football]]}} {{MedalGold|[[2011 Military World Games|Rio 2011]]|[[World Military Cup - Men's tournament|Team Competition]]}} | club-update = 00:00, June 21, 2015 (EST) | nationalteam-update = 00:00, June 21, 2015 (EST) }} '''Lyès Saïdi''' (born August 24, 1987 in [[Sidi Aïch]]) is an [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|footballer]] who last played for [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1]] club [[MC Oran]].
==Club career== In the summer of 2009, Saïdi signed a two-year contract with [[JS Kabylie]], joining them on a free transfer from ORB Akbou.<ref>[http://www.depechedekabylie.com/sport/71569-jsk-permettre-gagner-des-titres.html “La JSK va me permettre de gagner des titres”]</ref><ref>[http://www.lebuteur.com/ligue-1/actualites/jsk-saidi-et-akkouche-font-leur-bapteme-du-feu JSK : Saïdi et Akkouche font leur baptême du feu] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403220029/http://www.lebuteur.com/ligue-1/actualites/jsk-saidi-et-akkouche-font-leur-bapteme-du-feu |date=2012-04-03 }}</ref>
On May 2, 2011, Saïdi started for [[JS Kabylie]] in the [[2011 Algerian Cup Final]] against [[USM El Harrach]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/fiche-5585.php USMH 0-1 JSK] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203044759/http://www.dzfoot.com/fiche-5585.php |date=2013-12-03 }}</ref> JS Kabylie went on to win the game 1-0 with Saïdi playing the entire game. It was his first title with the club.
==Honours== * Won the [[Algerian Cup]] once with [[JS Kabylie]] in [[2010–11 Algerian Cup|2011]] * Won the [[World Military Cup]] once with the [[Algeria military national football team]] in 2011
